Package RRPSS

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Customer
    An Object of Customer represents a single customer with relevant customer details such as name, contact number and membership status.
    CustomerCollection
    The class is a entity class consisting the collections of Customer Objects
    CustomerFile
    The class represents as a boundary class which interacts with the external customer database
    CustomerMgr
    This class deals with managing the Customer Database of the restaurant And facilitates other managers to link with respective customers such as orderMgr and ReserVationMgr
    Dessert
    This class is a MenuItems(Inheritance) and represents all food of type Dessert
    Drink
    This class is a MenuItems(Inheritance) and represents all food of type Drinks
    Employee
    Entity class for an Employee of the Restaurant
    EmployeeCollection
    The class is a entity class consisting the collections of Employee Objects
    EmployeeFile
    The class represents as a boundary class which interacts with the external Employee database
    EmployeeMgr
    A manager class that handles the Employee Entities: assigns employees and removes assigned employee from tables
    FileReader
    The class is used when the system restarts to read all the Customer,Reservation,Employee and Menu Data files.
    MainCourse
    This class is a MenuItems(Inheritance) and represents all food of type Main Course
    MainMenu
    This Class handles the implementation of the MainMenu and the resulting changes that the user can do to the said Menu.
    MainMenuFile
    The class represents as a boundary class which interacts with the external Menu database
    MainMenuMgr
    This class deals with the overall Management of the MainMenu Class and MenuItems and its subsidiary classes
    MenuItems
    This class is the basic/template class on which MenuItems such as MainCourse/Dessert/Drink/Package are created
    Order
    The entity class of Order made by staff on the system
    OrderCollection
    The class is a entity class consisting the collections of Order Objects
    OrderFile
    The class represents as a boundary class which interacts with the external order database
    OrderMgr
    Manages orders sent by the staff to the kitchen.
    Package
    This class is a subclass of the MenuItems which wholly deals with the constituents of the Package (consisting of multiple MenuItems and the details of the Package)
    Reservation
    An object of the Reservation Class specifies the parameters of a single Reservation such as number of people who are catered to by the reservation, name of the customer creating the Reservation and the time of the specified Reservation
    ReservationMgr
    A manager class that handles the Reservation Entities, reads and writes reservations to file that stores the employees, checks table availabilities and capacity, checks, removes, and creates reservations, checks expiry of reservations and other related functions.
    ReservationsFile
    The class represents as a boundary class which interacts with the external Reservations database
    RestaurantApp
    A Restaurant App deals with the management of all the classes and all the ManagerClasses and facilitates the functioning of the Restaurant
    SalesRevenueReport
    Generates the sales revenue report for the restaurant according to day, month and year
    TableGenerator
    A This entire class helps to faciliate printing neat and tidy tables for our contents
    TableReservations
    An Object of TableReservations represents a Table with the Unique Table Identifier, Capacity, empty state identifier and List of Reservations associated with that Table
    TableReservationsCollection
    The class is a entity class consisting the collections of TableReservations Objects
